nd instabilities of gender, class, race and national identity. This accessible, extensively researched book will be of interest to all those interested in social, cultural or gender history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCrime and the press. 0aFemale offendersxHistoryy20th centuryvCase studies. 0aNineteen twenties. 0aPopular culturezEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex customszEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex rolezEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aTrials (Sex crimes)zEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aTrialsxHistoryy20th centuryvCase studies. 0aWomenxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxLegal status, laws, etczEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxPublic opinionxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenzEnglandxSocial life and customsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aadultery.  across-dressing.  adrugs.  afemale dancer.  alesbianism.  alibel case.  amagistrate-court trials.  amiscegenation.  amodern femininity.  amorality tales.  amurder.  apost-war womanhood.  asensational trials.  asexual ignorance.  asexual perversion.  avirgin birth.  ayoung female protagonists.1 aBland, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779896140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847798961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847798961/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles